AB  - We compare major factor models and find that the Stambaugh and Yuan () 4-factor model is the overall winner in the time-series domain. The Hou, Xue, and Zhang () q-factor model takes second place and the Fama and French () 5-factor model and the Barillas and Shanken () 6-factor model jointly take third place. The pairwise cross-sectional R2 and the multiple model comparison tests show that the Hou et al. () q-factor model, the Fama and French () 5-factor and 4-factor models, and the Barillas and Shanken () 6-factor model take equal first place in the horse race.
